                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="a1">
                           <locus target="#2r">Fol. 2r</locus>: Unidentified säläm-hymn for St. Mary (?).  <q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 2r: ርግብ፡ ሰላማዊት፡ ወንጽር፡ መንፈስዊት፡ ሰ፡ ለ፡ በሥምረተ፡ አብ፡ ወወልድ፡ ወመንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ሰ፡ ለ፡ እምትካት፡ የኀረየኪ፡ ሰ፡ ለ፡ በኵሉ፡ ጊዜ፡ ጽልዮተኪ፡ በጽሐ፡ ከመ፡ ኢይሙት፡ ገብርኪ፡…</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           Written by the same hand as that of Additio 2 (same as that of the main text?), in one column.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#204v">Fol. 204v</locus>: Unidentified text.<q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 204v: ኦእግዚእየ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ወልድ፡ ዋህድ፡ ቃለ፡ እግዚአብሔር። አብ፡ ዘበተከ፡ እምኔነ፡ ኵሎ፡ ማዕሠ(ረ)፡ ኃጣውኢነ፡ በሕማማቲከ፡ መኅየዊት፡ ወመድኀኒት፡ ዘነፋሕከ፡ ላዕለ፡ ገጸ፡ አርዳኢከ፡ ቅዱሳን፡ ወላዕከኒከ፡ ንጹሐን፡ ወትቤሎሙ፡ ንሥኡ፡ መንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ሰእለ፡ ኃደግሙ፡ ለሰብእ፡ ኀጢአተ።… </q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           Note on how Jesus broke the bounds of sins by means of His Passion, and how He blew upon the apostles and ministers faces the Holy Spirit, in order to redeem mankind from sins. The same hand as that of Additio 1 (the same as that of the main text?).
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Excerpts of hymns for the Good Friday (?) added in the upper margins of fols. 122v, 123r, 123v, 127v, 128r.&#xD;
- Crude notes written in blue, red pen and pencil on fols 4r, 33v, 34v, 51r, 52r, 53v, 55v, 103, 148v, 154v, 171v, 173v.&#xD;
- The words ʾǝläf kämäḉärräšaw are written, framed by dots, in the margin between columns on fol. 13r.&#xD;
- Numbers (?) are added between columns on fols 37v, 44r, 49v and in the left margin of fol. 76r.&#xD;
- Tämälläs-signs (in the shape of +) indicating the place where the omissions, written in the margin, or interlineally, belong: fols. 28r, 33r. &#xD;
- Immediate corrections marked by thin lines below words (e.g. fols. 32ra, 54va, 63vb, 84va, 113vb) and by thin lines above (fol. 128vb).&#xD;
- Omissions or corrections are written interlineally, e.g., fols. 13va, 13vb, 20ra, 48ra, 68vb, 80ra, 106rb, 132vb.&#xD;
- Unfilled spaces left for rubrication on fols. 2r (Additio 1), 203va, 204rb, 204v (Additio 2).&#xD;
- Lacuna in fol. 72rb: the text interrupts on fol. 72ra and resumes on fol. 72va.&#xD;
- The scribe reduced the size of the script on fols. 161vb-162rb.</item>
